The Chronicle Online Reporter President Mnangagwa has received his Covid-19 vaccination in the resort town of Victoria Falls where he launched the Second Phase of the national vaccination programme. Leaders from 23 parties in the country also received the jab, as the nation vigorously pursues its mission to have 60 percent of the population vaccinated against a pandemic that knows no political affiliation. <img class="alignnone wp-image-537920 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/03/ed-jab.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/03/ed-jab.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/03/ed-jab-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> In the Second Phase of the national vaccination programme, residents of the countryâ€™s premium tourism city will also be vaccinated for free on a voluntary basis, so as to reopen the critical sector that has been adversely affected by the pandemic. In his address the President urged the nation to accept the Covid-19 vaccines jabs as they are key to the opening of the economy. 